<p><a href="https://www.nintendo.com/en-gb/News/2025/December/Games-coming-to-Nintendo-Switch-2-and-Nintendo-Switch-in-2026-2988191.html?srsltid=AfmBOorqaFl-TsLqsyWkZbSTvzxSVDzlQDxQoJkvg07hOfjOBxWXICjT">Nintendo has a fairly busy year ahead for Switch 2</a>. Games arriving soon include an updated Switch 2 version of <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/animal-crossing-new-horizons">Animal Crossing: New Horizons</a> next week (15th January), <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/final-fantasy-7-remake-intergrade">Final Fantasy 7 Remake Intergrade</a> on 22nd January, and Dragon Quest 7 Reimagined on 3rd February.</p><p>Later in the year there's Pokémon Pokopia (5th March), Tomodachi LIfe: Living the Dream (spring), Yoshi and the Mysterious Book (spring), Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave (2026), and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/fromsoftwares-the-duskbloods-is-bloodborne-meets-sekiro-meets-dark-souls-with-jetpacks-and-dinos-thrown-in">FromSoftware's Switch 2 exclusive The Duskbloods</a> (2026). That's in addition to various third-party games and ports of big existing games.</p>
